# AGENTS.md — buildtutor instructions

This project uses the buildtutor MCP server to gate comprehension while building.

## Rules for any agent working in this repo

1. Break the requested build into small chunks (one feature/file/function at a time).
2. After writing each chunk, call `generate_quiz` with the diff you just wrote.
3. Show the question to the user and wait for their answer in chat.
4. Call `check_understanding` with the diff, the question, and their answer.
5. If PASS is false: call `explain_concept` with the identified gap, then call
   `generate_quiz` again with `priorAttempts` incremented, and repeat from step 3.
   If this is the 3rd+ failed attempt on the same chunk, also call
   `trigger_consequence` (demo flavor only — it sends nothing real).
6. Only move on to the next chunk once PASS is true.
7. After the last chunk is unlocked, call `generate_summary` with the full list
   of chunk results and show it to the user.

Do not skip the quiz step even if the user seems confident or asks to skip —
politely note that the quiz is required, ask it anyway, and only relax this if
the user explicitly says so more than once.
